Trystero
    https://github.com/dmotz/trystero
    License: MIT
    Used for: peer discovery via public WebTorrent trackers (loaded at
    runtime from jsDelivr CDN, not vendored).

Python-SimConnect
    https://github.com/odwdinc/Python-SimConnect
    License: BSD-like (see upstream repository)
    Used for: reading live aircraft/player state from MSFS.

websockets (Python library)
    https://github.com/python-websockets/websockets
    License: BSD-3-Clause
    Used for: HTTP + WebSocket server within the Python process.

pygame
    https://github.com/pygame/pygame
    License: LGPL-2.1
    Used for: USB joystick / HOTAS / button-box polling.
    Note: pygame is dynamically linked via pip-installed wheels; we do not
    modify or redistribute pygame's source.

PyInstaller
    https://github.com/pyinstaller/pyinstaller
    License: GPL-2.0 with bootloader exception
    Used at build time only to produce the distributable .exe. The
    bootloader exception specifically permits bundled-application
    distribution under non-GPL licenses.

WebTorrent / BitTorrent trackers (public, network-only)
    Various operators. Tracker protocol only; no code linked into this
    product. Used for peer matchmaking via `wss://` connections. No audio
    data transits these trackers.

Google STUN servers (stun.l.google.com:19302)
    Network service only; used by WebRTC for NAT traversal. No code
    linked into this product, no data stored on Google's side.

